460. dolia... releui : ‘ Ι rubbed the pitch (relino) off all my jars of wine.' Delium is the large jar—sometimes containing 18 amphorae—into which new wine was put previous to its being drawn off into the amphorae in which it was kept. The dolium was made of baked earth.
